episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob and Patrick are sent to jail in the underground tunnels of Glove World, leading to a daring escape.
Mr. Krabs has a secret taste for something… surprising.
Where Plankton usually dumps his rotten chum is too full, so he tricks SpongeBob into hiding it around the city.
Plankton’s giant Chum Bucket glove runs wild in town, but SpongeBob has a handy friend to help them out.
The newly reformed "Clean Bubble" takes a dishwashing job at the Krusty Krab, where he is tempted by the grime.
The Gal Pals take Pearl to a cabin in the woods for a weekend of silly pranks.
Plankton becomes a ghost to steal the secret formula, but requires a few lessons from the Flying Dutchman.
Squidward gleefully switches jobs with a bus driver for an easy ride… until SpongeBob and Patrick climb aboard.
Patrick takes a job at the Goofy Goober when he finds out the employees get free ice cream.
Patrick takes a job at the Goofy Goober when he finds out the employees get free ice cream.
SpongeBob and Squidward take a delivery to a dreaded town where the laws of logic no longer apply.
SpongeBob takes his first break ever at work, but how will he spend his precious time?
Squidward closes the gap in SpongeBob’s teeth, which causes a dramatic and unexpected change in his demeanor.
Karen quickly learns that kids grow up too fast after her new child arrives in the mail.
Plankton creates a clone of himself and Mr. Krabs, but neither restaurant is safe from the newcomer.
Sandy narrates the nocturnal adventures of Gary and his secret pal – Spot.
Gary is given a set of limbs to keep up with SpongeBob, but soon makes his owner look sluggish by comparison.
Old Man Jenkins disrupts business as usual at the Krusty Krab, but Mr. Krabs can’t find a way to kick him out.
SpongeBob breaks his precious alarm clock, but nothing else is loud enough to wake him up on time.
SpongeBob and Patrick volunteer as guards at the museum, while Squidward attempts to hang his painting unnoticed.
SpongeBob gets in over his head when he volunteers to babysit Sandy's 3 nieces.
SpongeBob befriends a small storm cloud, but has to protect it from a crazed weather man.
Plankton practices ruling the world by shrinking himself down and declaring himself king of SpongeBob’s aquarium.
Mr. Krabs turns the Krusty Krab into a jailhouse after Plankton breaks the law, but crime only pays for so long.
Patrick takes his grime to a new extreme, playing around in so much trash that he becomes unrecognizable.
Patrick inducts SpongeBob into his prestigious society of dullards and doofuses.
A weird moon turns everyone in the city into wild animals, and Sandy is the only one who can save them. Patrick sleepwalks and SpongeBob can't wake him up.

Patrick has a coupon for free ice cream, but he has to get to the store if he wants to use it; Mr. Krabs buys Squidward's art, but to make a profit on his purchase, he will have to get the artist out of the picture.

When SpongeBob mistakes an escaped convict for his driving instructor, it's the new teacher who learns a lesson; Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob in search of a missing toy, and SpongeBob finds himself lost in the lost-and-found.
SpongeBob must figure out how to do his job after accidentally shrinking himself; Squidward invents a new sport to get back at SpongeBob and Patrick for annoying him.
Plankton decides to close the Chum Bucket and move to a new town, but Mr. Krabs still suspects he is up to something./SpongeBob accidentally picks up King Neptune's magic trident.
A misunderstanding leaves Spongebob and Patrick to think Life Insurance will protect them from any danger; Spongebob blows himself a bubble boat, and Mrs. Puff tries to stop Spongebob.

When SpongeBob cooks at home, Mr. Krabs' customers leave his restaurant and head for SpongeBob's Place. When Plankton gets kicked out of the house, it's up to SpongeBob to teach him how to win his computer wife back.
SpongeBob imitates everyone for fun, but it goes too far once SpongeBob gets "Mocking Mimicry Madness"/A worm named Prickles goes inside SpongeBob, and brings uninvited guests.
when spongebob and patrick get a new game called whirlybrains, they run into some trouble.
SpongeBob fears that he is allergic to his pineapple house and Squidward offers to help him find a new home.

SpongeBob and Patrick get hooked on the latest fad - flying your own brain like a tiny drone! When SpongeBob & Patrick play Mermaidman and Barnacleboy, it's all fun and games until their sworn enemies arrive.

episodes.episodeTitle: Mutiny on the Krusty/The Whole Tooth
episodes.episodeDescription: When the Krusty Krab is blown away by a storm, an insane Mr. Krabs has to guide his employees and customers back to their homes. Patrick is forced to lose his last baby tooth, but he is frightened.

When SpongeBob hides the secret formula in his home, it's up to Gary to protect it from Plankton. When a freak accident causes everyone in town to become as stupid as Patrick, Sandy must save the day.

The gang heads to a food convention, but things go awry when they become stranded in the woods. SpongeBob accidentally fibs to his pen pal, but when his friend comes to visit, he must keep the ruse going!

Sandy creates the latest acorn-based food sensation, but her tree pays the price for her greed. SpongeBob erects a community bulletin board in the Krusty Krab, but anonymous reviews posted on it lead to trouble.
Plankton realizes that fortune cookies can predict the future, so he changes them to fit his plans.
SpongeBob and Patrick see a commercial and believe their houses are sold.
Plankton clones SpongeBob to steal the secret formula, but his plans may be ruined by the original SpongeBob.

In "Mall Girl Pearl," Pearl must find a job to be cool like her friends, but, the only place hiring is the mall's lamest store. In "Two Thumbs Down," SpongeBob loses the use of his thumbs, making his life difficult.
Sandy tries to study SpongeBob and Patrick's behavior, but her science experiment goes horribly awry. Mr. Krabs takes Plankton's advice, and finally marries the only thing he ever loved...money!
SpongeBob gets a pair of long pants, but they change his life in unexpected ways. When Larry the Lobster opens a new gym in Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob becomes his best customer.

episodes.episodeTitle: Patrick! The Game/The Sewers of Bikini Bottom
episodes.episodeDescription: Patrick invents a new board game, and invites SpongeBob, Sandy and Squidward to play it with him. After accidentally flushing Mr. Krabs' safe, SpongeBob and Squidward must go into the sewers to find it.
Patrick enters a krabby patty eating competition in order to defend Bikini Bottom's honor.

Company Picnic: In order to boost morale, Mr. Krabs throws a company picnic - On the same day Plankton is hosting his own. Pull Up a Barrel: It's a stormy day in Bikini Bottom while SpongeBob and Squidward are at work, so Mr. Krabs tells them stories of his days in the Navy.

Squid Plus One: Squidward gets invited to a gallery opening and wants to take someone, but can't decide who. The Executive Treatment: Patrick takes on a career of business when he tries to order a special sandwich.

Lost in Bikini Bottom: On his way to work, SpongeBob attempts to take a shortcut to get there quicker, only to find himself in an abandoned area of Bikini Bottom, and unable to find his way out. Tutor Sauce: After failing his drivers test, SpongeBob consults Mr. Krabs for driving lessons.
In order to save money, Mr. Krabs fires SpongeBob; however, unable to just "do nothing", SpongeBob decides to go back to work, no matter what - or where.
Spongebob is desperate to meet his newest hero, Kenny the Cat. Mr. Krabs tries to scare Squidward into working harder.
SpongeBob and Patrick go to see the latest horror film, only to be seemingly stalked by the villain.SpongeBob holds a sÃ©ance at the Krusty Krab to learn the recipe for a long-lost sandwich.

Mr. Krabs gets trapped in Bikini Bottom's brand-new bank, and it's up to SpongeBob & Patrick to save him.After failing again to steal the Krabby Patty formula, Plankton gets a pet to cheer himself up.

What do microwave ovens, dry cleaning, corn dogs and purple floaty things have in common? They can all destroy Bikini Bottom, that's what! But will they? Find out in this spine-tingling SpongeBob SquarePants adventure, It Came From Goo Lagoon! Horrors.

An imprisoned Plankton teams up with his fellow inmates to break out of jail and steal the Krabby Patty secret formula. / SpongeBob replaces his broken spatula with one from Plankton, which may or may not have magical powers.
SpongeBob finds a nasty sea urchin living in the Krusty Krab, and tries everything to force it out. After getting his groceries stolen, Squidward convinces SpongeBob and Sandy to teach him karate.
Squidward finds SpongeBob's diary, and starts reading it out loud in the Krusty Krab.SpongeBob once again fails his driving test, forcing Mrs. Puff to think outside the box--and off the road.
SpongeBob must return to the Milkshake Academy after he realizes his Milkshake License has expired. / Squidward suffers a head injury and gets the mind of an infant.

Patrick becomes the superhero Patrick-Man, who intends to clean up Bikini Bottom--whether it wants it or not! Gary becomes obsessed with his new red ball, forcing SpongeBob to take drastic measures to intervene.
Sandy is determined to break a record number of world records, in record time, so SpongeBob joins her for an action-packed weekend of dangerous record setting.

SpongeBob and Patrick make a bet to see who can hold a "funny face" the longest...then their faces freeze that way!SpongeBob and Patrick spend one last glorious - and dangerous - day at Glove World before it closes for good.

When Squidward goes home sick with a fake illness, SpongeBob HypochondriacPants thinks he's caught it for real!Mrs. Puff finally finds a use for SpongeBob's reckless driving and enters him in the Demolition Derby!

When Plankton replaces his computer wife Karen with the new, better Karen 2, the original Karen ends up working at the Krusty Krab. / SpongeBob can't get to sleep, and asks for help from Patrick... who can't stay awake.

SpongeBob brings home a box of new snail treats that Gary will do anything to get - especially when they run out. / Plankton wins a free Krabby Patty, and Mr. Krabs will do anything to stop him from collecting.
Mr. Krabs is forced to give out free food to win back customers
Colonel Carper wants to give a vacation to SpongeBob and Squidward. It fails when stupid Mr. Krabs comes and takes all of Carper's equipment.
SpongeBob needs all of his friends to help him remodel his pineapple.
SpongeBob and Patrick find a houseboat haunted by a crew of ghost pirates--and get caught in the feud between them and the Flying Dutchman.

episodes.episodeTitle: House Sittin' for Sandy/Smoothe Jazz at Bikini Bottom
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob house-site for Sandy; SpongeBob and Squidward go to the Kelpy G concert.
SpongeBob and Patrick learn the secret origins of Mermaid Man and Branacle Boy from the heroes themselves. Plankton grows himself a second eye sing SpongeBob's DNA, and becomes nice.

Barnacle Face: The night before the big school dance, Mr. Krabs asksSpongeBob to help Pearl get rid of a barncealce on her face.Pet Sitter Pat: When SpongeBob gets invited to his Grandma's birthdayparty, he asks Patrick to pet-sit Gary.

All of Bikini Bottom enters a sleigh race to win $1 million. While racing, they are attacked by the abominable snow mollusk. Plankton takes advantage of everyone being gone to steal the Krabby Patty secret formula.

When Squidward gets hurt on the job, he threatens to take legal action unless Mr. Krabs agrees to cater to him hand and foot. Mr. Krabs and Plankton find a common enemy in the popular new "Flabby Patty" restaurant.

episodes.episodeTitle: Squidward's School for Grown Ups/Oral Report
episodes.episodeDescription: When Patrick suddenly grows a very grown-up beard, he decides it's time to act like a grown-up and perhaps Squiward is the perfect squid to help him!While preparing to give an oral report SpongeBob comes down with stage fright.
SpongeBob and Patrick build an indoor miniature golf course in SpongeBob's house./SpongeBob has trouble throwing anything away when he realizes how many memories are attached to all his possessions.
SpongeBob and Patrick build an indoor miniature golf course in SpongeBob's house./SpongeBob has trouble throwing anything away when he realizes how many memories are attached to all his possessions.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Krabby Patty That Ate Bikini Bottom/Bubble Buddy Returns
episodes.episodeDescription: Mr Krabs uses Sandy's experimental growth formula on a Krabby Patty with disastrous results.SpongeBob tries to keep Bubble Buddy's visiting son, Shiny, out of trouble and away from sharp edges.
SpongeBob and Patrick take a friendship test./Pearl is embarrassed when she must sit next to SpongeBob in the Tunnel of Glove.
Madam Hagfish puts a hex on the Krusty Krab, and SpongeBob and Patrick search for a legendary drain on the ocean floor.
Madam Hagfish puts a hex on the Krusty Krab, and SpongeBob and Patrick search for a legendary drain on the ocean floor.

episodes.episodeTitle: New Fish in Town/Big Sister Sam
episodes.episodeDescription: Patrick's big sister Samantha comes for a visit./Sandy and Plankton bond over their shared love.
SpongeBob orders a product that will help him learn to say no; SpongeBob gets a song stuck in his head.

Patrick wants to take a vacation, but can't afford one--until SpongeBob comes up with the perfect solution: a "staycation"!Mr. Krabs and SpongeBob win a free cruise thanks to Plankton, who secretly goes with them to try to steal the Krabby Patty formula.

episodes.episodeTitle: Krusty Dogs/The Wreck of the Mauna Loa
episodes.episodeDescription: Mr. Krabs decides to start selling hot dogs instead of Krabby Patties./SpongeBob and Patrick discover a lost ship.
Squidward sculpts a statue of Mr. Krabs for The Krusty Krab./Giant sea whelks terrorize the folks of Bikini Bottom.
SpongeBob, Patrick and Squidward are accidentally locked in Bikini Bottom's first time capsule./SpongeBob and Patrick build a dream world for Squidward.

SpongeBob and the gang, including Patrick, Mr. Krabs, Squidward, Sandy Cheeks, Plankton and Karen, and Gary, participate in a sled worm race for one million dollars. However, just before the race begins, Plankton sneaks off to the Krusty Krab and uses a robot as his replacement in the race.

episodes.episodeTitle: You Don't Know Sponge/Hide and Then What Happens
episodes.episodeDescription: Plankton masquerades as Gary to steal the Krabby Patty formula./SpongeBob and Patrick play Hide N' Seek and SpongeBob searches the world for Patrick.

Instead of paying to patch up a hole in the wall of the Krusty Krab, Mr. Krabs decides to use it to make more money by turning it into a drive-thru window.Tony Fast, Jr., the son of a famous race car driver, teaches SpongeBob how to drive.

When Squidward gets hurt on the job, he menaces to take legal action unless his employer, Mr. Krabs, agrees to cater to him to his every need. Mr. Krabs, who eventually gets tired of doing everything for Squidward, hires SpongeBob and Patrick to investigate the scene.
SpongeBob and Patrick build a dream Tiki World for Squidward
Patrick's big sister Samantha comes for a visit./Sandy and Plankton bond over their shared love.

episodes.episodeTitle: New Fish in Town/Love That Squid
episodes.episodeDescription: A new fish named Howard moves into the neighborhood, and Squidward wants to befriend him. Howard hates "jelly-fishing bubble-blowers", so Squidward tries to keep SpongeBob and Patrick away from him at all costs. However, Howard gets infected by SpongeBob and Patrick's jellyfishing and bubble-blowing personalities.

episodes.episodeTitle: Krusty Dogs/The Wreck of the Mauna Loa
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob invents the "Krusty Dog" out of leftover Krabby Patty ingredients. It becomes very successful, which makes Mr. Krabs to remove the Krabby Patties from the menu. SpongeBob becomes upset and tries several attempts to get the sandwich back at the menu.

episodes.episodeTitle: You Don't Know Sponge/Tunnel of Glove
episodes.episodeDescription: Spongebob is frustrated when Patrick can't remember any information about him. A ride at Glove World stops working, leaving Pearl stranded inside with Spongebob.
Squidward bets SpongeBob he can't go a day without crying.Mrs. Puff has to work through her summer break at the Krusty Krab.

episodes.episodeTitle: Hide and Then What Happens?/Shellback Shenanigans
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob tells Patrick that they should play hide-and-seek. However, Patrick does not know what hide-and-seek is or how to play it, so SpongeBob teaches him. When they start playing, SpongeBob cannot find Patrick, so he sets out on an adventure, searching the whole town and other proximate places to find him.

SpongeBob couldn't say "no" when everyone needs his help, rendering him unable to go to Glove World with Patrick, so Gary orders an "abrasive side" for him. At first, SpongeBob thinks the abrasive side is working well, but soon falls upon hardships as the evilness when the abrasive side takes him over.
Mr. Krabs finds out that Plankton's afraid of whales.Gary falls for a snail named Mary.
SpongeBob and Patrick dig a tunnel between their two houses and drive Squidward nuts.Pat learns just enough karate to wreak havoc in Bikini Bottom.
Includes three extra bonus shorts after the episode. SpongeBob, Patrick and Plankton solve a mystery on a runaway train.
Squidward, who is dubbing himself as "the most miserable person in Bikini Bottom", complains about everything around him when another, more serious problem arises in the form of a volcanic eruption.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Curse of the Hex/The Main Drain
episodes.episodeDescription: After forbidding her to order as the restaurant is closed, an evil hagfish known as Madame Hagfish becomes furious and curses the Krusty Krab. The next day, unnatural events occur at the restaurant, which concerns Mr. Krabs. As a result, Mr. Krabs and SpongeBob set out to find the hagfish in hope that she would lift the curse.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Monster Who Came to Bikini Bottom/Welcome to the Bikini Bottom Triangle
episodes.episodeDescription: Squidward's complaints trigger a volcanic eruption./SpongeBob and Patrick search for a drain on the ocean floor./A monster terrorizes Bikini Bottom./All the Bikini Bottom citizens disappear.

episodes.episodeTitle: Gramma's Secret Recipe/The Cent of Money
episodes.episodeDescription: Plankton disguises himself as SpongeBob's grandmother.Mr. Krabs uses Gary to find spare change.
Mr. Krabs opens a Dinner Theater at the Krusty KrabSpongeBob takes his pals to Texas to see Sandy in a squirrel rodeo.
Mr. Krabs finds out that Plankton's afraid of whales.Gary falls for a snail named Mary.
Squidward bets SpongeBob he can't go a day without crying.Mrs. Puff has to work through her summer break at the Krusty Krab.

episodes.episodeTitle: Back to the Past/The Bad Guy Club for Villains
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob and Patrick go back in time to see the young Mermaidman and Barnacleboy.SpongeBob and Patrick watch their heroes fight bad guys in a classic Mermaidman and Barnacleboy episode.
SpongeBob and Patrick protest the construction of a highway that would destroy Jellyfish Fields.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Curse of Bikini Bottom/Squidward in Clarinetland
episodes.episodeDescription: When Squidward requires Mr. Krabs to give him extra space for his clarinet, he is forced to share a locker with Spongebob. But, his paranoia drives him "literally" crazy.
SpongeBob and Patrick buy a toy and have to learn to share it./SpongeBob goes with Mr. Krabs to the Cheapest Crab Convention.

episodes.episodeTitle: Keep Bikini Bottom Beautiful/A Pal for Gary
episodes.episodeDescription: Squidward cleans up the city of Bikini Bottom with 'help' from SpongeBob.SpongeBob brings Gary a pet that terrorizes him.
Greasy Buffoons: Mr. Krabs and Plankton woo customers with greasy entrees. Model Sponge: SpongeBob tries a career at being a model in a kitchen sponge commercial.

episodes.episodeTitle: Someone's in the Kitchen with Sandy/The Inside Job
episodes.episodeDescription: Someone's in the Kitchen with Sandy: Plankton steals Sandy's fur to disguise himself as Sandy and get the Krabby Patty formula. The Inside Job: Plankton goes inside SpongeBob's head to get the Krabby Patty formula.
Growth Spout: Mr. Krabs tries to find enough food to feed Pearl as she goes through her growth spurt. Stuck in the Wringer: After showering, SpongeBob gets stuck in his wringer.
Tenacle-vison: Squidward becomes the star of his own public access TV show. I Heart Dancing: Squidward tries to sabotage SpongeBob's big dance audition.
King Neptune hosts a party, inviting all of the sea creatures. SpongeBob is jealous of the royal chef.

Plankton discovers an underground cave which he decides to convert into part of the Chum Bucket. The Chum Buket becomes popular because of the great scenery and threatens to put the Krusty Krabs out of business.
The cast look back on major events in their lives; Patchy hosts a star-studded anniversary special.

Chum Bucket Supreme: None of Plankton's intellectually advanced advertising slogans for the Chum Bucket seem to be working. Plankton decides to switch gears by hiring someone who can create the dumbest slogans ever-Patrick!

episodes.episodeTitle: Sand Castles in the Sand/Shell Shocked
episodes.episodeDescription: Sand Castles in the Sand: SpongeBob and Patrick decide to celebrate their friendship by enjoying a day at the beach together. But what starts out as a fun day for the two best buddies quickly turns into all-out war when SpongeBob and Patrick use their sandcastles to battle each other.

episodes.episodeTitle: No Hat for Pat/Toy Store of Doom
episodes.episodeDescription: No Hat for Pat: Patrick is sick of all of his friends not being able to play with him because they have to put on their Krusty Krab hats and go to work. So when Mr. Krabs offers him a job as a sign-holder, Patrick is thrilled because it means he gets to wear a hat and work with all his friends!
Gullible Pants: SpongeBob is left in charge of the Krusty Krab while Mr. Krabs steps out for 15 minutes, and he is determined to make it the best-managed 15 minutes ever!

Pets or Pests: SpongeBob adopts a stray worm, and to his surprise, the worm gives birth to some worm babies overnight! But since Gary won't play nice, SpongeBob needs to find loving homes for his new slimy, weird-looking friends.
A-SpongeBob and Patrick get carried away when they fill in for Mermaidman and Barnacleboy. B-Squidward poses as the teacher at a prestigious music school.

episodes.episodeTitle: Squid's Visit/To Squarepants or Not to Squarepants
episodes.episodeDescription: Spongebob's pants have shrunk in the dryer, so he buys some new, round pants, but no one recognises him.
Grandpappy the Pirate: Mr. Krabs' granddad is coming to town! But instead of being excited, Mr. Krabs is nervous because his swarthy pirate granddad thinks that Mr. Krabs is a pirate, too.

Dear Vikings: There's a new Viking-themed promotion at the Krusty Krab, so SpongeBob is determined to find out everything there is to know about Vikings. And what better way to find out about Vikings than to talk to them himself?

Krusty Krushers: Mr. Krabs hatches up yet another get-rich-quick scheme: professional wrestling! But Mr. Krabs isn't the one who's going to wrestle. He's going to be the manager and  money-handler-for the newest tag-team wrestlers in Bikini Bottom: SpongeBob and Patrick!
Porous Pockets: When SpongeBob suddenly becomes the richest citizen of Bikini Bottom, he finds himself surrounded by lots of new "friends" who are more than happy to help him spend his money.

episodes.episodeTitle: SpongeBob SquarePants vs. The Big One
episodes.episodeDescription: Spongebob and his friends are swept away by a giant wave and find themselves stranded on a remote tropical island. In order to get home, they must learn how to surf from enigmatic surf guru: Jack Kahuna Laguna.

The Slumber Party: Pearl's getting ready for her slumber party, but Mr. Krabs' meddling in the party preparations is getting out of control. Pearl forces him out of the house and orders him to stay at SpongeBob's house until the party's over.

Boating Buddies: In an attempt to get away from SpongeBob, Squidward drives off in his boat as fast as he can. But he's stopped in his tracks when he's pulled over by a cop and is ordered  to go to boating school. Now Squidward has to sit next to SpongeBob in class all day long and SpongeBob couldn't be happier!

The Patty Caper: The Krabby Patty formula has been placed in a vault far away for safe keeping. When Mr. Krabs forgets the recipe, he gives SpongeBob the key to the vault and sends him on a train ride to retrieve the formula. But someone steals the key!
Giant Squidward: When Squidward gets spritzed with plant growth spray, he becomes monstrously huge. SpongeBob and Patrick are thrilled because they now have a giant buddy to play games with.

episodes.episodeTitle: A Life in a Day/Sun Bleached
episodes.episodeDescription: A Life in a Day: Everyone is in awe of Larry the Lobster's daredevil ways, especially SpongeBob and Patrick. Patrick decides that it's time for them to start living like Larry, but spongeBob isn't so sure.
SpongeBob tries to remove a splinter before Mr. Krabs learns about it and sends him home early; SpongeBob and Patrick get new slide whistles and keep playing them, much to the annoyance of Squidward.

Not Normal: When Squidward points out to SpongeBob that he's not normal, SpongeBob makes it his mission to become normal. SpongeBob begins to lose all his spongey-ness, and it's not long  before he's completely unrecognizable, even to his best friends.
Spongicus: Plankton has demolished the Chum Bucket! In its place, he has built a Roman coliseum and announces there will be a gladiator show, which means togas, chariots, and ferocious lionfish.
Penny Foolish: When Mr. Krabs sees SpongeBob pick a penny up off the street, he becomes obsessed with the coin and vows to have it in his possession no matter what it takes.

House Fancy: Squidward is enraged when he sees the home of his rival, Squilliam featured on a TV show about fancy houses. Determined not to be outdone, Squidward arranges to have his own house on the program.

episodes.episodeTitle: Banned in Bikini Bottom/Stanley S. SquarePants
episodes.episodeDescription: Banned in Bikini Bottom: SpongeBob loves Krabby Patties so much, he just can't help singing and dancing when he's around the delicious sandwiches. But Miss Priss, who is against all things fun and delicious, is appalled by his behavior and has Krabby Patties banned from Bikini Bottom!

The Two Faces of Squidward: Squidward is rushed to the hospital when SpongeBob accidentally slams the door on Squidward's face. He undergoes surgery to have his face fixed to look normal again-but things don't go exactly as planned.

Whatever Happened to SpongeBob? (WhoBob WhatPants): When SpongeBob tries to spend some quality time with his friends, he just ends up being a nuisance to everyone instead. They all tell him to go away, so with a heavy heart, SpongeBob decides to do just that-he packs up to leave Bikini Bottom forever.

episodes.episodeTitle: 20,000 Patties Under the Sea/The Battle of Bikini Bottom
episodes.episodeDescription: 20,000 Patties Under the Sea: SpongeBob and Mr. Krabs turn an old submarine into a mobile Krusty Krab. Not to be undone by his competitor's new gimmick, Plankton responds with his own traveling Chum Bucket, and the two rival restaurants engage in an undersea battle complete with torpedoes, a giant sea monster and chum.

Pest of the West: While researching his family tree SpongeBob discovers that he was related to the great Western hero, and famous chili-slinger, SpongeBuck. The tale of his ancestor's fame begins in the town of Dead Eye Gulch, which used to be called Bikini Gulch before the no-good Dead Eye Plankton came along.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Inmates of Summer/To Save a Squirrel
episodes.episodeDescription: The Inmates of Summer: Instead of getting on the ship headed for summer camp, SpongeBob and Patrick accidentally board a ship full of prisoners on their way to jail on Inferno Island. To Save a Squirrel: SpongeBob and Patrick stow away on one of Sandy's extreme wilderness expeditions.

Blackened Sponge: While trying to wrestle open the cap off of a tube of toothpaste SpongeBob accidentally punches himself in the face leaving behind a hideous black eye. Too embarrassed to tell anyone the truth behind the shiner, SpongeBob makes up a tale about a fight with a giant thug.
Picture Day: It's Picture Day for the Boating School Year Book, and SpongeBob has spent all morning getting ready for it. Now all he has to do is make it to Boating School without getting dirty.
When two halves of an ancient medallion reunite, SpongeBob and his friends find themselves in the city of Atlantis, where the king gives them a tour.

Goo Goo Gas: Plankton plans on making Mr. Krabs helpless by turning him and the rest of the Krusty Krab staff into babies with a gas he created. Le Big Switch: After being enrolled in a chef exchange program, SpongeBob switches places with a snooty French chef from a high-end restaurant.

episodes.episodeTitle: A Flea in Her Dome/The Donut of Shame/The Krusty Plate
episodes.episodeDescription: A Flea in Her Dome: Sandy comes back from Texas with fleas and SpongeBob and Patrick try to help Sandy rid her Tree Dome of them. The Donut of Shame: When Patrick accidentally takes SpongeBob's donut he is wracked with guilt over his heinous crime.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Krusty Sponge/Sing a Song of Patrick
episodes.episodeDescription: The Krusty Sponge: SpongeBob becomes the latest local obsession after a notable food critic gives him high ratings. Now Mr. Krabs is looking to cash in on the fad by making everything in the Krusty Krab Sponge-themed.

episodes.episodeTitle: Money Talks/SpongeBob vs. The Patty Gadget/Slimy Dancing
episodes.episodeDescription: Money Talks:Mr. Krabs makes a wish that he could talk to money. When his wish is magically granted, Mr. Krabs learns (to his horror) what all of his dollars, pennies and quarters have been longing for: they want Mr. Krabs to spend them.

episodes.episodeTitle: To Love a Patty/Breath of Fresh Squidward
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob has trouble letting go of a perfect krabby patty; Squidward's personality changes when his security fence electrocutes him.

Roller Cowards: The scariest roller coaster ever has just opened at Bikini Bottom's amusement park. At first SpongeBob and Patrick are determined to ride this monster coaster. But the more they think about how scary it is the more they chicken out.

New Digs: After arriving one minute late for work, SpongeBob decides to move into the Krusty Krab so that he will never be late to work again. Krabs a la Mode: When Plankton secretly turns down the thermostat at the Krusty Krab the entire restaurant freezes over.

Spy Buddies: Determined to uncover Plankton's next devious plot, Mr. Krabs sends SpongeBob and Patrick to spy on him. Boat Smarts: Watch an instructional video on the best (and worst) boating techniques as demonstrated by Squidward and SpongeBob.

Rise and Shine: Take a look inside Patrick Star's rock where we see that his morning routine is anything but ordinary. Waiting: SpongeBob discovers that his breakfast cereal has an offer for free toy.

The Original Fry Cook: Mr. Krab's old fry cook pays a special visit to the Krusty Krab. SpongeBob is in awe of his predecessor, who has since become a world renowned chef following his departure from Krabs' restaurant.

Mr. Krabs and Plankton have been business rivals and bitter enemies for longer than anyone can remember, but, one day, during another one of Plankton's failed attempts at stealing the Krabby Patty formula, Mr. Krabs reveals that they were not always this way.

episodes.episodeTitle: Best Day Ever/The Gift of Gum
episodes.episodeDescription: Best Day Ever: SpongeBob is going to have the best day ever. First he gets to work at the Krusty Krab. Then he is going to meet Sandy for a little Ka-Ra-Tay, followed by jellyfishing with Patrick, and Squidward's clarinet recital.

The Pink Purloiner: SpongeBob's favorite jellyfishing net is missing! And worst of all, Patrick may have been the one that stole it. But SpongeBob can't accuse his friend of anything until he can find some hard evidence that the starfish does indeed have the net.

Born to be Wild: SpongeBob hears that a ferocious biker gang is coming to town, only no one in Bikini Bottom seems bothered by the news. So SpongeBob dons his leather jacket, warms up his bike, and prepares to protect the town all by himself.

Driven to Tears: SpongeBob has failed his driving test-again. Patrick is so outraged by the injustice of it all that he storms into the testing facility and takes the test to prove that it is an unfair test and impossible to pass.

The Thing: After a freak bicycling accident, Squidward is coated in so much mud, leaves, branches and gunk to make him totally unrecognizable. The residents of Bikini Bottom think that Squidward is some sort of monster come to terrorize the town.

Squidtastic Voyage: When Squidward swallows his clarinet reed Sandy offers to retrieve the piece by shrinking herself and a mini sub down to microscopic proportions and traveling into Squidward's body.
Bummer Vacation: Mr. Krabs is about to be fined for unfair labor practices. It turns out that in all the years he has been working at the Krusty Krab, SpongeBob has never taken a vacation.

New Leaf: In the battle for fast food supremacy, Plankton has decided to throw in the towel and start a new business selling trinkets and souvenir gifts. He even renames his store from The Chum Bucket to The Chumporium.
All That Glitters: During an intense day on the job, SpongeBob's spatula breaks mid patty-flip. With his favorite kitchen implement out of commission, SpongeBob searches for a temporary  replacment.
Mr. Krabs wants to throw a birthday party for Pearl; SpongeBob receives an invitation to take part in a competition.

Ghost Host: The Flying Dutchman takes up residence at SpongeBob's house where he proceeds to scare, startle and surprise SpongeBob around the clock. Eventually all the spooky shenanigans grow old, and SpongeBob is no longer afraid of the Dutchman.
Mr. Krabs turns the Krusty Krab into a hotel; SpongeBob's record of failed boating tests caused Mrs. Puff to lose her job.
Patrick SmartPants: Patrick becomes smart after getting hit on the head. SquidBob TentaclePants: Sandy's experiment turns Squidward and SpongeBob into one body.

episodes.episodeTitle: Enemy In-Law/Mermaidman and Barnacleboy VI: The Motion Picture
episodes.episodeDescription: Enemy-In-Law: Mr. Krabs' Mom is dating again, and it seems like things could be serious. Mr. Krabs tries to be happy for his mother, but he is absolutely horrified when he learns that the that the secret paramour is his arch-rival Plankton!

Dunces and Dragons: After a freak jousting accident at a Medieval Times-style restaurant, SpongeBob and Patrick are transported to a medieval version of Bikini Bottom. There they are mistaken for great knights and sent on a quest by King Krabs to rescue his daughter, the Princess Pearl, from the clutches of the evil wizard Planktonamor.

Selling Out: Mr. Krabs sells his restaurant to a conglomerate that plans to turn the Krusty Krab into a big corporate chain. At first the sell out brings the kind of peace and quiet Mr.Krabs always wanted.

Skill Crane: When a Skill Crane is installed in the Krusty Krab, Squidward becomes obsessed with winning a stuffed animal from the machine. It's not long before he spends all of his money nd the deed to his house on the Skill Crane-and still he can't win anything.

Have You Seen This Snail?: While trying to beat a paddle-ball world record, SpongeBob forgets to feed Gary-for several weeks. So Gary runs away to downtown Bikini Bottom where he is taken in by a kindly old woman who confuses him with one of her many deceased pets.

the Lost Mattress: SpongeBob hears that Mr. Krabs cannot get a good night sleep on his lumpy mattress, so, with the help of Patrick and Squidward, SpongeBob buys Mr. Krabs a brand new mattress and throws the old one away.

episodes.episodeTitle: Fear of a Krabby Patty/Shell of a Man
episodes.episodeDescription: Fear of a Krabby Patty: The Krusty Krab is now open 24-hours-a-day, which means that the Krusty Krab employees have to work round-the-clock and without a break. At first the prospect of never leaving work is like a dream come true for SpongeBob.

episodes.episodeTitle: SpongeBob Meets the Strangler/Pranks a Lot
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob Meets the Strangler: SpongeBob catches someone littering and turns him in to the police - but it's the Tattletale Strangler! The Strangler escapes custody and disguises himself as SpongeBob's bodyguard, all the while looking for a moment to strangle him.

episodes.episodeTitle: Lost Episode (The Sponge Who Could Fly)
episodes.episodeDescription: Lost Episode (The Sponge Who Could Fly): SpongeBob is jellyfishing when he wistfully realizes that he wants to fly with the jellyfish. He proceeds to come up with numerous ways to fly. He and Patrick try everything from constructing a plane to tying SpongeBob to a kite.

Missing Identity: SpongeBob has lost his name tag! He has no idea where it has gone. He retraces all of his steps, with "help" from Patrick, but to no avail. His mind and day rapidly deteriorating, he continues to search desperately until, miraculously, Patrick spots the missing identification.

Krabby Land: It's summer break, and Mr. Krabs wants to squeeze every penny out of the children who are out of school. He take a pile of rusty old junk and concocts a playground of sorts, and promises them that if they pay to play and eat Krabby Patties, Krabby the Klown will appear to entertain them.

episodes.episodeTitle: Born Again Krabs/I Had an Accident
episodes.episodeDescription: "Born Again Krabs": Mr. Krabs refuses to let SpongeBob throw away a moldy Krabby Patty that was festering under the grill. He tries to pawn it off on customers to save the fifty-two cents he would have lost if he threw the patty away.
The Great Snail Race: Squidward gets a pure-bread snail, Snelle, and decides to race her in the snail races. SpongeBob becomes competitive and enters Gary, coaching him to the point of exhaustion.

SpongeBob B.C. (UGH): It is prehistoric Bikini Bottom, and we spend a day in the life of SpongeGar, Patar, and Squog. (Sponge, Pat, and Squidward's prehistoric alter-egos.) Thanks to the magic of an underwater thunderstorm, our three Neanderthal friends discover fire.

New Student Starfish: It's another day of boating school for SpongeBob, and this time, Patrick wants to come along too. Patrick becomes the new student in SpongeBob's class, and from his  introduction, begins getting SpongeBob in trouble.

episodes.episodeTitle: Chocolate with Nuts/Mermaidman and Barnacleboy V
episodes.episodeDescription: Chocolate with Nuts: SpongeBob and Patrick want to make some extra cash so they decide to sell chocolate bars door to door. They have no luck at first. In fact, they end up buying more stuff than selling stuff.

SpongeBob's House Party: SpongeBob, while grocery shopping, discovers a "how to throw a party" kit. He decides to throw a big party and invites everyone he's ever known. Unfortunately for his guests, SpongeBob plans everything right down to the minute, sapping all the fun from his party.

Wet Painters: SpongeBob and Patrick are wreaking havoc on the Krusty Krab, so Mr. Krabs decides to give them a little busy work. He tells them to paint his living room, and gives them  permanent paint.

Krab Borg: SpongeBob stays up late one night watching a sci-fi film where robots take over the world. He comes to work paranoid and Squidward scoffs at him. Through a series of wild coincidences, SpongeBob gets it in his head that Mr. Krabs is a robot and convinces Squidward the same thing, too.

No Weenies Allowed: SpongeBob and Sandy are enjoying a day at the beach when they come across the Salty Spitoon, a rough and tumble hangout for real rugged folk. Sandy makes it through the bouncer, but SpongeBob is left outside.

episodes.episodeTitle: As Seen on TV/Can You Spare a Dime?
episodes.episodeDescription: As Seen on TV: Krabs makes a low budget commercial and SpongeBob is in it for one second. After the commercial airs once at three in the morning, a blind man recognizes SpongeBob.
Snowball Effect: When it snows in Bikini Bottom, SpongeBob and Patrick go out in the snow and play in their snow forts etc... They make a racket and Squidward complains.
Mermaidman and Barnacleboy IV: Mermaidman and Barnacleboy are eating at the Krusty Krab when Mermaidman accidentally drops his utility belt. SpongeBob finds the belt and can't resist it.
Nasty Patty: Mr. Krabs and SpongeBob hide the health inspector's body. Idiot Box: SpongeBob and Patrick throw out a TV to play in the box.
Just One Bite: When SpongeBob learns that Squidward has never actually tried a Krabby Patty, he becomes obsessed with the idea that Squidward must try it. He badgers Squidward until he gives in.

Club SpongeBob: SpongeBob and Patrick build a small clubhouse in a tree and get inside. When Squidward happens by they tell him he can't join the club because he wouldn't fit in. Pissed, Squidward insists on joining the club. He climbs the tree and gets inside.

episodes.episodeTitle: The Algae's Always Greener/SpongeGuard on Duty
episodes.episodeDescription: Plankton invents a device that allows him to switch lives with Mr. Krabs. / SpongeBob wants to become a lifeguard.

episodes.episodeTitle: Sandy, SpongeBob, and the Worm/Squid on Strike
episodes.episodeDescription: Sandy, SpongeBob & The Worm: A large worm is terrorizing Bikini Bottom and SpongeBob is terrified of it. Sandy thinks SpongeBob is chicken and drags him out into the wilderness to take the  worm on.
Jellyfish Hunter: When money hungry Mr. Krabs discovers that customers love SpongeBob's special jellyfish jelly Krabby Patty, he convinces Spongebob to bring him as many of the jellyfish as he can.

Sailor Mouth: SpongeBob reads a "bad" word off the dumpster behind the Krusty Krabs and he doesn't know what it means. He asks Patrick who explains to him that it's a fancy word and both of them start using it in every sentence they can.
SpongeBob attempts to write an 800-word essay before morning; Patrick tries to impress his parents on Starfish Day.

the Krusty Krab is open for 24 hours a day to make more money, and Squidward scares Spongebob with the "hash slinging slasher."/ Ms. Puff comes to the Krusty Krab and Mr. Krabs gets Spongebob's help to woo her.
The Secret Box: Once Patrick and SpongeBob is not the same, he hasn't opened yet. Band Geeks: Squidward is back, welcome to the band, Squidward and other friends are going to the band.
Welcome to the Chum Bucket: SpongeBob goes to work at the Chum Bucket. Frankendoodle: SpongeBob creates SpongeDoodle, who plays pranks on everyone, forcing him to erase him.

Shanghaied: An anchor gets lodged into Squidward's window, so SpongeBob, Patrick and Squidward all climb the rope to see who is responsible. It's The Flying Dutchman's ship, and he enslaves  them to work as crew members on deck for the rest of their lives!

Pressure: Sandy and SpongeBob get into a fierce competition doing extreme underwater sports. The longer they compete, the more people they attract and soon SpongeBob has a small following who cheer him on as their underwater mascot and poo poo Sandy because she is a "land lubber."

Mermaidman and Barnacleboy III: When Mermaidman and Barnacleboy go away for the weekend, they ask SpongeBob and Patrick to house sit for them. Inside the house, SpongeBob and Patrick  discover the evil super villain, Man-Ray frozen in a tank.

episodes.episodeTitle: No Free Rides/I'm Your Biggest Fanatic
episodes.episodeDescription: SpongeBob gets extra credit in order to pass his driving test. SpongeBob and Patrick go to a jellyfishing convention.
Survival of the Idiots: SpongeBob and Patrick sneak into the Treedome. Dumped: Gary goes to Patrick, and SpongeBob becomes jealous.

Christmas Who?: Nobody in Bikini Bottom has ever heard of Christmas or Santa Clause until Sandy lets them in on this surface tradition. SpongeBob wants to bring Christmas to Bikini Bottom this year and his enthusiasm is infectious.
Pre-Hibernation Week: SpongeBob hides from Sandy. Life of Crime: SpongeBob and Patrick borrow a balloon from a store and accidentally pop it.
SpongeBob gets embarrassed when his grandma kisses him in public. / Squidward moves into a gated community.
SpongeBob and Patrick watch over Sandy's pets when she is out of town. / SpongeBob has an idea, but nobody will listen.
Squidward thinks he has given SpongeBob an exploding pie. / Plankton builds a robot that looks like Mr. Krabs.
Patrick tries to win an award. / SpongeBob gets a new friend.
SpongeBob realizes he can't tie his shoes. / Mr. Krabs puts Squidward in charge for a day.
Spongebob's breath starts to stink. / Mr. Krabs employs his daughter at the Krusty Krab.
Hooky: When the mysterious "hooks" (fishing, that is) suddenly appear in Bikini Bottom, Mr. Krabs warns SpongeBob to stay away from them.
SpongeBob has fun on April Fool's Day. / SpongeBob and Patrick visit a museum.
SpongeBob and Patrick try to help Sandy out when she feels homesick. / Plankton tries to get SpongeBob to be mean.
Mr. Krabs convinces SpongeBob and Patrick to join him on a treasure hunt; SpongeBob gets on the wrong bus.
SpongeBob and Patrick go to the carnival. / SpongeBob has fun with a gum wrapper.
SpongeBob visits his friends' dreams. / SpongeBob comes down with a case of the Suds.
Squidward accidentally travels through time. / Mr. Krabs bans SpongeBob from doing karate.

episodes.episodeTitle: Scaredy Pants/I Was a Teenage Gary
episodes.episodeDescription: Scaredy Pants: Halloween party. I Was a Teenage Gary: Squidward takes care of SpongeBob's pet snail.

The Chaperone: When Mr. Krab's daughter Pearl is stood up for her prom, SpongeBob agrees to step in. Not wanting Pearl to feel bad about her date, SpongeBob tries to make himself tall, dark and handsome.
SpongeBob orders a pair of fake muscles to impress his friends. / Squidward pretends that he is a ghost.
A talent show is held at the Krusty Krab. / SpongeBob spends time with Plankton.
Nature Pants: After suffering through some unusually rough days at work, SpongeBob decides to leave his industrialized life and "live off the land" with the jellyfish in JellyFish Fields. A...
Sandy's Rocket: Sandy Cheeks takes a rocket into space. Squeaky Boots: Mr. Krabs gives SpongeBob noisy boots.
Hall Monitor: SpongeBob takes his turn as hall monitor. Jellyfish Jam: SpongeBob takes a wild jellyfish home.
Mermaid Man and Barnacle Boy: SpongeBob and Patrick visit a retirement home. Pickles: SpongeBob loses his confidence.
Pizza Delivery: SpongeBob and Patrick are stranded in the desert. Home Sweet Pineapple: SpongeBob loses his pineapple home.
Naughty Nautical Neighbors: Squidward turns SpongeBob and Patrick against each other. Boating School: SpongeBob goes to boating school.
Jellyfishing: SpongeBob and Patrick take Squidward jellyfishing. Plankton!: Plankton tries to steal the formula.
Bubblestand: SpongeBob blows bubbles. Ripped Pants: SpongeBob accidentally tears his pants.

episodes.episodeTitle: Help Wanted/Reef Blower/Tea at the Treedome
episodes.episodeDescription: Help Wanted: SpongeBob attempts to get a job as a fry cook. Reef Blower: Squidward's lawn. Tea at the Treedome: SpongeBob meets Sandy Cheeks.
